post_text: Is there a plan? Are we working on one? When will we know the plan? We know it is frustrating to not have all the answers! How we return to school will depend on requirements and guidance from local and state officials. Thanks for your patience! #nrvikings

The high school is starting a "Ask Franklin" column in our Viking Vault. This is similar to Dear Abby.

Our first "Ask Franklin" question was "Prom is coming up. What is a good/creative way to ask a boy/girl to prom?"

Franklin's answer? "Roses are red, donuts are the bomb, do me a favor and come with me to prom." And we think adding the "prom" donuts wouldn't hurt either. ;)

We encourage inquiries for Franklin when seeking advice. Individuals can inquire through email to: dmincks@northridgevikings.org
#NRVikings

The 5th Grade Beginning Band is finishing up preparations for their annual March Concert!

The band learned how to play the French nursery rhyme ‚ÄúFr√®re Jacques.‚Äù The students learned how to play this song in a round where different instruments are playing different notes at the same time to make harmonies in the music.

They have to be able to play their part accurately and independently, while also listening to how their part fits into the others around them. These students just picked up their instruments for the first time in September and are learning how to read music while also performing with correct posture, breathing, and playing techniques. This is where it all begins!

Come see the 5th Grade Beginning Band and all other Northridge Middle/High School Bands and Choirs perform on Sunday, March 1st in the high school auditeria. Band starts at 3:00 pm and Choir starts at 4:30
pm. We hope to see you there! #NRVikings
